=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_RLPFD_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 60 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 60.1513
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.6070
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0028
  pitch_clarity: 152.6799
  inharmonicity: 0.0020
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -26.3344
  resonance_freq: 172.2656

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: RLPFD Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/RLPFD.html
// Tags: RLPFD, Classes, filter
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ RLPFD.ar(Mix(LFSaw.ar([120, 180], 0, 0.33)), LinExp.kr(LFCub.kr(0.1, 0.5*pi), -1, 1, 280, 1500), 0.6, 0.5, mul:3).dup }.play
